sequenceDiagram
    participant R as Requester
    participant M as Manager
    participant FD as Finance Director
    participant P as Procurement
    participant V as Vendor
    participant F as Finance

    R->>M: Submit purchase request
    M-->>R: PR approved

    %% ⚡ CHANGED SECTION - SOX spend threshold control point
    alt Amount > $50,000 (SOX Control: Segregation of Duties)
        M->>FD: Route for second approval (threshold exceeded)
        FD->>FD: Review spend justification & budget
        FD-->>M: Second approval granted
        M->>P: Forward approved PR (Manager + Finance Director approved)
    else Amount ≤ $50,000
        M->>P: Forward approved PR (Manager approved)
    end
    %% ⚡ END CHANGED SECTION

    P->>V: Issue Purchase Order
    V-->>P: Order confirmation
    V->>F: Submit invoice
    F->>F: 3-way match verification
    F-->>V: Payment processed (NET30)

%% EXPLANATION:
%% Added a Finance Director participant and an alt/else branch immediately after Manager approval. Purchases over $50,000 are routed to the Finance Director for a second approval before reaching Procurement, while purchases at or under $50,000 continue directly to Procurement. The threshold value and SOX rationale are explicitly labeled in the diagram so auditors can clearly identify the control point.